Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve, peel and chop the @Echalion Shallot{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium-high heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, fry the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and shallot until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @mixed herbs{1%sachet} and cook for ~{1%min} more. Add the @risotto rice{175%g}, then stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Pour in the @boiled water for the risotto{600%ml} and @vegetable stock paste{20%g}. Stir in the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and bring back to the boil.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}). Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the stock has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g}.

While the risotto bakes, halve the @lemon{1/2}(halved and squeezed) and squeeze the lemon juice into a large #bowl{}.

Add the @sugar for the dressing{1%tsp} and @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp} to the bowl and mix together. Set aside.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, a squeeze of lemon, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and @?butter{1%knob}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the bowl of dressing and toss to coat.

Share the chicken risotto between your #plates{} or #bowls{} and serve with the salad alongside. Sprinkle over the grated Cheddar to finish.

Enjoy!